-- UBS Appoints Amy Lo as Head of Ultra High Net Worth in Asia-Pacific Region
-- B y   J o y c e   K o h
-- 2010-10-05T00:28:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/ubs-appoints-amy-lo-as-head-of-ultra-high-net-worth-in-asia.html
UBS AG appointed Amy Lo as head of
ultra high net worth business in Asia-Pacific with effect from
Jan. 1, according to an internal memo obtained by Bloomberg
News.   Lo will report jointly to Kathryn Shih, chief executive
officer of wealth management in Asia-Pacific, and Josef Stadler,
global ultra high net worth head.  Lo, who is currently regional market manager and head of
ultra high net worth in Hong Kong, will be succeeded by Jean-
Claude Humair and Francis Liu. Humair is currently head of UBS
wealth management in Japan, and Liu was Merrill Lynch & Co.â€™s
